Israel army 'regrets' damage to Tehran synagogue






                The Israeli military on Tuesday expressed regret over what it called "collateral damage" to a synagogue in Tehran caused by an overnight strike.&nbsp;

The strike, the Israeli military said, was targeting a senior Iranian commander.&nbsp;

