Erdogan condemns 'treacherous attack' in Istanbul






                Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan on Tuesday condemned what he described as "treacherous attack" outside the Israeli consulate in Istanbul where a gunman was killed, and vowed to fight "terrorism".&nbsp;

"We will continue our fight against all kinds of terrorism, and we will not allow ... provocations to harm Turkey's climate of security," Erdogan said in a televised speech.&nbsp;

